```csharp
options.SignIn.RequireConfirmedAccount = true;
```
to:
```csharp
options.SignIn.RequireConfirmedAccount = false;
```

## 4. NavMenu — Replace `Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor`

Keep the same structure but replace the nav links with:
- Home (/)
- Patients (/patients)
- Appointments (/appointments)
- Billing (/billing)
- Keep the AuthorizeView login/logout section as-is

## 5. Pages — Create the following Razor component files:

### `Components/Pages/Home.razor` — Replace existing
Dashboard showing today's appointments count, total patients, pending invoices. Use `@attribute [Authorize]`.

### `Components/Pages/Patients.razor` — Patient list with search, link to add/edit
### `Components/Pages/PatientDetail.razor` — View/edit pet details and treatment notes (route: /patients/{id:int})
### `Components/Pages/PatientForm.razor` — Add/edit pet + owner (route: /patients/new and /patients/{id:int}/edit)
### `Components/Pages/Appointments.razor` — Calendar-like view showing weekly schedule, create/reschedule/cancel
### `Components/Pages/Billing.razor` — Invoice list, create invoice, process payment, payment history

ALL pages must have `@attribute [Authorize]` and `@rendermode InteractiveServer`.

For the Appointments page, show a week view with time slots (8am-6pm). Highlight booked slots. Allow clicking to create an appointment. Show a modal/form for creating and editing. When an appointment is created/cancelled, the calendar updates in real-time.

For Billing, allow selecting an owner, adding line items, generating invoice. Show payment form to record payments against invoices.

Make all forms functional with proper validation using EditForm and DataAnnotationsValidator.

## 6. Delete unnecessary files
- Delete Components/Pages/Counter.razor
- Delete Components/Pages/Weather.razor

## 7. After all files are created, run:
```bash
cd /tmp/sv-88c8fcb0c2cd48268930b8d448a056cc/VetClinic
# Delete old DB and migrations to start fresh
rm -rf Data/Migrations Data/app.db
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
dotnet build
```

Make sure the build succeeds. Fix any errors.

